==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sensitometer
<hw>Sen`si*tom"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Sensitive</er>; <er>-meter</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Photog.)</fld> <def>An
instrument or apparatus for comparing and grading the sensitiveness of
plates, films, etc., as a screen divided into squares of different
shades or colors, from which a picture is made on the plate to be
tested.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sensitory</ent>⟦br⟧
